  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Sunday. Today Sophia decided it was finally time to teach me her culture's cooking, whether I was ready or not.",
      "zh": "星期天。今天 Sophia 終於決定該教我她那一套文化裡的煮菜功夫了，不管我準備好了沒。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"A person should know at least one dish from their own family before they turn thirteen,\" she announced, tying an apron around my waist.",
      "zh": "「一個人不到十三歲，至少應該學會一道自己家裡的菜，」她一邊宣布，一邊幫我繫上圍裙。"
    },
    {
      "en": "This is, apparently, an old family custom, passed down through so many generations that nobody remembers exactly when it started.",
      "zh": "這顯然是一個老家規矩，一代一代傳下來，久到沒有人記得確切是從什麼時候開始的。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Some traditions do not need a reason,\" Sophia said, when I asked why we always add ginger to everything. \"They just need respect.\"",
      "zh": "「有些傳統不需要理由，」我問她為什麼每道菜都要加薑的時候，她這麼回答：「它們只需要尊重。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Before we even touched the stove, Sophia set the table with proper manners in mind: chopsticks placed just right, a spoon for the soup, nothing crooked.",
      "zh": "在我們碰到爐子之前，Sophia 先按照規矩擺好桌子：筷子擺得剛剛好，湯匙放在旁邁配湯用，沒有一樣是歪的。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"In a proper home, the table looks neat before the food even arrives,\" she said, straightening a chopstick that looked perfectly fine to me.",
      "zh": "「在一個規矩的家裡，食物還沒上桌，餐桌就應該整整齊齊，」她一邊說，一邊把一根其實看起來很正常的筷子擺得更直。"
    },
    {
      "en": "She lit a small stick of incense at the little shelf near the kitchen, a quiet custom for the elders who came before us.",
      "zh": "她在廚房旁邊的小神桌前點了一炷香，這是為了紀念先我們而去的長輩的一個安靜習俗。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"This is not really about religion,\" she explained. \"It is about remembering people who are not here to eat dinner with us anymore.\"",
      "zh": "「這其實跟宗教沒有太大關係，」她解釋：「這是關於記得那些已經不能跟我們一起吃晚飯的人。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "I found that surprisingly gentle, coming from someone who yells at William for touching the rice cooker wrong.",
      "zh": "從一個會因為 William 用錯方式碰電鍋就對他大吼的人口中聽到這種話，讓我覺得意外地溫柔。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia boiled water in an old ceramic teapot that has been in the family longer than my parents have been married.",
      "zh": "Sophia 用一個比我爸媽結婚年紀還久的舊陶瓷茶壺燒了水。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"This teapot is basically ancient,\" I said, and she laughed and said it had survived three house moves and one very clumsy uncle.",
      "zh": "「這個茶壺根本是古董，」我說，她笑著說這個茶壺撐過了三次搬家，還有一位手很笨的叔叔。"
    },
    {
      "en": "We chopped vegetables together, and she showed me the proper way to hold a knife, gentle but firm, like everything else in her kitchen.",
      "zh": "我們一起切菜，她教我拿刀正確的方式，輕柔但穩定，就跟她廚房裡的每件事一樣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William wandered in, hoping for a snack, and Sophia handed him a small task instead: washing rice like an obedient little helper.",
      "zh": "William 晃進來想找點心吃，Sophia 卻塞給他一個小任務：像個聽話的小幫手一樣去洗米。"
    },
    {
      "en": "He complained for exactly one minute before deciding that washing rice with his hands underwater was actually kind of fun.",
      "zh": "他抱怨了整整一分鐘，後來覺得把手泡在水裡洗米其實還滿好玩的。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"See?\" Sophia said, generous with her praise for once. \"Even a naughty boy can learn to obey the kitchen.\"",
      "zh": "「看到了嗎？」Sophia 難得慷慨地稱讚了一句：「就算是調皮的男孩，也能學會聽廚房的話。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "When Bernice's family stopped by for a visit, Sophia instantly switched into full host mode, offering tea before anyone had even said hello properly.",
      "zh": "後來 Bernice 一家人來拜訪，Sophia 立刻切換成完整的待客模式，大家連好都還沒打完，她已經先端出茶了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "A good host, according to Sophia, always makes a guest feel like the most important person in the room.",
      "zh": "根據 Sophia 的說法，一位好的主人，永遠要讓客人感覺自己是這房間裡最重要的人。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice's grandmother recognized the teapot immediately and the two of them talked about old cultural customs for almost an hour.",
      "zh": "Bernice 的阿嬤一眼就認出那個茶壺，兩人聊起舊時的文化風俗聊了將近一個小時。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I mostly understood one word out of every five, but I could tell it was a conversation full of respect for the past.",
      "zh": "我大概每五個字只聽得懂一個，但我看得出來，這是一段充滿對過去尊重的對話。"
    },
    {
      "en": "By the time dinner was ready, the whole kitchen smelled like ginger, soup, and something that felt distinctly like tradition.",
      "zh": "等到晚餐終於準備好，整個廚房聞起來都是薑、湯，還有一種清楚屬於傳統的味道。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Even William ate his vegetables without complaining, probably because he felt proud of the rice he had personally washed.",
      "zh": "連 William 都乖乖把蔬菜吃完，完全沒抱怨，大概是因為他對自己親手洗的米感到很有成就感。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Lesson of the day: some family rules are ancient, some are just Sophia's own invention, and honestly, it is hard to tell the difference.",
      "zh": "今日心得：有些家規是老祖宗傳下來的，有些根本是 Sophia 自己發明的，老實說，很難分辨兩者的差別。"
    }
  ],
